                                                    <p>Definitely one of the best games I've ever played. It took me a bit to figure out how to stay alive and take down the first few difficult enemy dino-bots, but once I got the techniques down, even dying felt really satisfying. That is an important quality for me, as someone who doesn't identify as a "gamer" but plays video games. I'm never gonna be one of those braggarts who insult anyone in the most juvenile and offensive way for not being on the same level of gaming. If I'm dying and having to wait through a loading screen on a modern game 40 times in a row, that's going to be really frustrating and take away from the enjoyment. With Horizon, I'll say it again: it was SATISFYING to get beat by the enemies and have to adjust tactics. Beyond that, the protagonist and storyline are rich and compelling.</p>
